  references  external links operationsedit tahoe resources has five operating mines escobal mine in southeast guatemala la arena gold mine in northern peru shahuindo gold mine in northern peru and the timmins west and bell creek mines in ontario canada in  tahoe achieved record silver production by producing  million ounces at allin sustaining costs of  per ounce the company also produced  ounces of gold at allin sustaining costs of  per ounce  in q  tahoe produced  million ounces of silver and  ounces of gold the company generated record earnings and cash flow from higher sales revenue and lower operating costs  escobal silver mineedit the escobal project is a highgrade silver discovery located in southeast guatemala approximately  km eastsoutheast of guatemala city in addition to silver the mine contains sizable reserves of gold lead and zinc tahoe resources acquired the project in mid from goldcorp for  million usd in stock and cash in november  tahoe resources released a preliminary assessment of the project completed by m engineering in  the escobal mine produced a record  million ounces of silver in concentrate as of january  it was estimated that the escobal mine contained indicated resources of  million silver ounces at an average grade of  grams per tonne gt along with significant quantities of lead zinc and gold proven and probable reserves are  million tonnes at an average grade of  gt silver containing  million ounces of silver figures such as these have caused mining experts to suggest that the escobal mine could become one of the largest silver producers in the world underground development on the mine began in may  and the exploitation license was granted in april  roughly  construction jobs were created with the mines development mining operations began in september  and the first precious metal concentrate shipment was sent on october   for the year ending december   tahoe resources announced that its net earnings for the year were  million share during  the company incurred  million in expenses for the escobal mine project commercial operations began in january  regional exploration in guatemala was suspended in  following the governments proposed moratorium on new exploration licenses exploration since that date has focused only on the  km granted concessions surrounding the escobal mine dialogue continues with the ministry of energy and mines to grant additional exploration licenses while community work continues in areas of exploration interest in july  tahoe announced that the supreme court of guatemala had issued a decision to temporarily suspend its escobal mining license in response to action brought by an antimining organization that claimed guatemalas ministry of energy and mines had violated the xinca indigenous peoples right of consultation in advance of granting the permit  la arena gold mineedit on february   tahoe resources announced a merger with rio alto mining owner of the la arena gold mine in northern peru for  billion the merger was completed on april   la arena produced a company record  ounces of gold in  beating estimates which was followed in  with production of  ounces of gold exceeding that previous record la arena is located  km northnorthwest of lima in the eastern slope of the western cordillera close to the continental divide at approximately  meters above sea level it contains two types of deposits oxide gold in brecciated sandstone as well as coppergold sulfide mineralization in january  measured and indicated oxide resources totaled  million tonnes with an average gold grade of  gt and proven and probable oxide reserves of  million tonnes with an average gold grade of  gt containing  ounces of gold meanwhile measured and indicated sulfide resources for the la arena deposit totaled  million tonnes with average gold and copper grades of  gt and  percent respectively proven and probable sulfide reserves are  million tonnes with average gold and copper grades of  gt and  percent respectively shahuindo gold mineedit in the merger between tahoe resources and rio alto mining tahoe resources took ownership of shahuindo gold project which rio alto had acquired from sulliden gold in august  construction began on the project in mid with commercial production anticipated to begin in the second quarter of  shahuindo is located in a prolific goldproducing area in northern peru  km north of the la arena mine on the west side of the condebamba river valley with topography varying from rolling hills to steep ravines its elevation ranges from  meters above sea level the world wildlife fund has designated this area as neotropical peruvian yungas the mines technical report dated january  reflects measured and indicated oxide resources of  million tonnes with an average gold grade of  gt containing  million ounces of gold proven and probable oxide reserves total  million tonnes with an average grade of  gt containing  million ounces of gold mineral reserves increased  percent over the previous technical report timmins west gold mineedit in the  merger between tahoe resources and lake shore gold tahoe resources acquired the timmins west mine located  km west of timmins ontario canada which in  was ranked the th largest goldproducing region in the world the mine contains three deposits the timmins deposit which has been in commercial production since january  the thunder creek deposit which achieved commercial production in january  and the  gap deposit approximately  meters from the thunder creek deposit which is under development as of this writing with commercial production expected in  all three deposits are connected by underground drifts the mine is located on one of the worlds most prolific gold camps and the mine property comprises an area of about  square km ore from the mine is accessed using mobile equipment via internal ramps both from the surface and the main shaft the mine currently produces  tonnes per day of ore which is trucked to the bell creek mill  km away for processing in  the mine produced  ounces of gold from  tonnes processed at an average gold grade of  gt in january  probable mineral reserves came to  million tonnes with an average gold grade of  gt containing  ounces of gold in january  tahoe reported it had discovered significant extensions of mineralization in the  trend deep timmins west bell creek vogel whitney and gold river zones in the timmins district of canada bell creek complexedit the bell creek complex was acquired by tahoe resources inc in the merger with lake shore gold in  it is located approximately  km northeast of timmins ontario and consists of an underground gold mine and a processing facility in january  the mine produced  ounces of gold from processing  tonnes at an average grade of  gt as of january   measured and indicated mineral resources for the bell creek deposit totaled  million tonnes with an average gold grade of  gt containing  ounces of gold proven and probable mineral reserves inclusive of mineral resources are  million tonnes with an average gold grade of  gt containing  ounces of gold a large resource at depth indicates a nearterm opportunity to expand production and extend the mines life the mill features a conventional gold mill circuit with crushing and grinding followed by carboninleach and carboninpulp processes for gold recovery a portion of gold is recovered by gravity before the leaching process awardsedit tahoe resources has received the following awards midcap winner best sustainability ethics and environmental governance program canadian society of corporate secretaries cscs  precious metals and mining topgun ceo awarded to kevin mcarthur brendan wood international  precious metals and mining topgun company brendan wood international  precious metals and mining topgun board brendan wood international  alleged role in violence related to escobal mine in edit local residents resistance to the escobal silver mine project led to violent clashes in spring  fears about pollution and water contamination and about potentially damaging effects to the way of life in the area which is primarily agricultural caused many local residents to protest the mines development the surrounding communities voted against the project in  but the vote was nonbinding and development proceeded in april  a series of protests began among residents of san rafael on the public road near the mine on april  seven people were shot when security guards working at the escobal mine opened fire on  protesters in a release issued on may   tahoe resources stated that the protesters were armed with machetes the media reported that alberto rotondo tahoe resources security chief for the escobal project was caught in a wiretap giving direct orders to murder local opponents of tahoes mining project on april  rotondo was arrested at la aurora airport in guatemala city apparently trying to flee rotondo was criminally charged in guatemala with obstruction of justice causing minor and serious injuries and mistreatment of a minor rotondo no longer works for tahoe resources the seven men who were shot filed a civil lawsuit garcia v tahoe resources inc against tahoe resources in june  alleging that rotondo ordered the shooting and that tahoe resources was legally responsible for the shooting the suit alleged assault aggravated assault and obstruction of justice and that the shooting was premeditated on november   the supreme court of british columbia stayed a judgment in favor of tahoe resources key peopleedit kevin mcarthur founder and executive chair ron clayton president and chief executive officer elizabeth mcgregor vice president and chief financial officer brian brodsky vp exploration tom fudge vp operations edie hofmeister vp corporate affairs charles v muerhoff vp technical services mark sadler vp projects development mark utting vp investor relations peter van alphen vp operations timmins board of directorsedit kevin mcarthur executive chair ron clay