ncome us million  total assets us billion  total equity us billion  website wwwtahoeresourcescom tahoe resources inc tsx tho nyse taho is a mining company and intermediate precious metals producer with silver and gold mines in canada guatemala and peru it was founded in vancouver bc by kevin mcarthur former ceo of glamis gold and goldcorp incorporated in british columbia canada the companys us headquarters is located in reno nevada in  the company acquired lake shore gold in ontario valued at  million cad making it a wholly owned subsidiary of tahoe resources and effectively adding lake shores timmins west and bell creek gold mines in ontario to tahoe resources assets which include mines in guatemala and peru the company employs more than  people worldwide tahoe resources is a publicly traded company in the industrial metals and minerals industry listed on the new york stock exchange and the toronto stock exchange in  tahoe resources was accused of using the guatemalan police and army violence to force its mining operation on the local communities tahoe is facing a criminal trial in guatemala and a civil lawsuit in canada for previous cases of alleged repression contents  operations  escobal silver mine  la arena gold mine  shahuindo gold mine  timmins west gold mine  bell creek complex  awards  alleged role in violence related to escobal mine in   key people  board of directors  offices  see also  references  external links operationsedit tahoe resources has five operating mines escobal mine in southeast guatemala la arena gold mine in northern peru shahuindo gold mine in northern peru and the timmins west and bell creek mines in ontario canada in  tahoe achieved record silver production by producing  million ounces at allin sustaining costs of  per ounce the company also produced  ounces of gold at allin sustaining costs of  per ounce  in q  tahoe produced  million ounces of silver and  ounces of gold the company generated record earnings and cash flow from higher sales revenue and lower operating costs  escobal silver mineedit the escobal project is a highgrade silver discovery located in southeast guatemala approximately  km eastsoutheast of guatemala city in addition to silver the mine contains sizable reserves of gold lead and zinc tahoe resources acquired the project in mid from goldcorp for  million usd in stock and cash in november  tahoe resources released a preliminary assessment of the project completed by m engineering in  the escobal mine produced a record  million ounces of silver in concentrate as of january  it was estimated that the escobal mine contained indicated resources of  million silver ounces at an average grade of  grams per tonne gt along with significant quantities of lead zinc and gold proven and probable reserves are  million tonnes at an average grade of  gt silver containing  million ounces of silver figures such as these have caused mining experts to suggest that the escobal mine could become one of the largest silver producers in the world underground development on the mine began in may  and the exploitation license was granted in april  roughly  construction jobs were created with the mines development mining operations began in september  and the first precious metal concentrate shipment was sent on october   for the year ending december   tahoe resources announced that its net earnings for the year were  million share during  the company incurred  million in expenses for the escobal mine project commercial operations began in january  regional exploration in guatemala was suspended in  following the governments proposed moratorium on new exploration licenses exploration since that date has focused only on the  km granted concessions surrounding the escobal mine dialogue continues with the ministry of energy and mines to grant additional exploration licenses while community work continues in areas of exploration interest in july  tahoe announced that the supreme court of guatemala had issu